Paper: hep-th/9310059

Date: 1993-10-12

Title: Dynamics of the Cosmological Constant in Two-Dimensional Universe

Authors: Izawa K.-I

Comments: PHYZZX, 6 pages, KUNS 1221

Journal-ref: Prog.Theor.Phys. 91 (1994) 393-396

We consider a two-dimensional model of gravity with the cosmological constantas a dynamical variable. The effective cosmological constant is derived whenthe universe has no initial boundary. It turns out to be extremely small if theuniverse is sufficiently large.